.SH NAME
SBO::Lib::Readme \- Routines for interacting with a typical SBo README file.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  use SBO::Lib::Readme qw/ get_readme_contents /;
\&
\&  print get_readme_contents($sbo);
.Ve
.SH SUBROUTINES
.IX Header "SUBROUTINES"
.SS ask_opts
.IX Subsection "ask_opts"
.Vb 1
\&  my $opts = ask_opts($sbo, $location);
.Ve
.PP
Users may be prompted to add options if saved options are not to be retrieved, provided
that a \f(CW\*(C`README\*(C'\fR file associated with the script contains a variable assignment of the
form \f(CW\*(C`WORD=\*(C'\fR (any case and accounts for quotes). The prompt appears if the SlackBuild
accepts the variable name from the environment, the \f(CW\*(C`README\*(C'\fR shows an example of
calling the SlackBuild with the variable or the phrase "to the script/SlackBuild"
follows.
.PP
An option string is returned, if set.
.SS ask_previous
.IX Subsection "ask_previous"
.Vb 1
\&  my $opts = ask_previous($sbo);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWask_previous()\fR takes the name of a SlackBuild and checks for saved options
under the \f(CW\*(C`/var/log/sbotools\*(C'\fR directory. If options have been saved, the user
is prompted for reuse. The saved options are returned if yes.
.SS ask_user_group
.IX Subsection "ask_user_group"
.Vb 1
\&  my $bool = ask_user_group($cmds);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWask_user_group()\fR takes the \f(CWuseradd(1)\fR and \f(CWgroupadd(1)\fR commands found in a
\&\f(CW\*(C`README\*(C'\fR file and calls \f(CWuser_group_do_not_exist()\fR; if at least one of the specified
users or groups does not exist, it prompts for running the commands. If yes,
the \f(CW$cmds\fR are returned, and \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR otherwise.
.SS display_readmes
.IX Subsection "display_readmes"
.Vb 1
\&  display_readmes($sbo, $location);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWdisplay_readmes()\fR checks for README files in \f(CW$location\fR. It displays \f(CW\*(C`README\*(C'\fR in
all cases, and additional files in alphabetical order upon a single prompt.
.SS get_readme_contents
.IX Subsection "get_readme_contents"
.Vb 1
\&  my $contents = get_readme_contents($location);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWget_readme_contents()\fR opens the README file in \f(CW$location\fR and returns
its contents. On error, it returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS get_user_group
.IX Subsection "get_user_group"
.Vb 1
\&  my @cmds = @{ get_user_group($sbo, $location, $opts) };
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWget_user_group()\fR searches the \f(CW\*(C`SlackBuild\*(C'\fR for \f(CW$sbo\fR in \f(CW$location\fR
for \f(CWuseradd(1)\fR and \f(CWgroupadd(1)\fR commands, and returns them in an array
reference. If no commands are found initially, it searches any \f(CW\*(C`README*\*(C'\fR
files for them.
.PP
Some SlackBuilds allow the user to set user and group names and ID numbers
with variables. Optionally pass an option string \f(CW$opt\fR if interactive or
if an existing build options file is to be used.
.SS user_group_do_not_exist
.IX Subsection "user_group_do_not_exist"
.Vb 1
\&  my @nonexistent = @{ user_group_do_not_exist(@cmds) };
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWuser_group_do_not_exist()\fR takes an array of sugested commands generated by \f(CWget_user_group()\fR,
returning those that do not exist on the system in an array reference.
.SS user_prompt
.IX Subsection "user_prompt"
.Vb 1
\&  my ($proceed, $cmds, $opts) = user_prompt($sbo, $location, $get_only);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWuser_prompt()\fR is the main point of access to the other commands in \f(CW\*(C`Readme.pm\*(C'\fR.
Except in the download\-only case, it calls subroutines to find options and commands,
and then prompts the user for installation. It returns the answer to the installation
prompt (true for \*(Aqyes\*(Aq and false for \*(Aqno\*(Aq), the list of commands and the list of
options.
.SS verify_user_group
.IX Subsection "verify_user_group"
.Vb 1
\&  my @cmds = verify_user_group(@preliminary_cmds);
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CWverify_user_group()\fR checks for required options and sanitizes \f(CW\*(C`useradd\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`groupadd\*(C'\fR commands found in \f(CW\*(C`SlackBuilds\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`README\*(C'\fR files. An array with
correct commands is returned.
.SH "EXIT CODES"
.IX Header "EXIT CODES"
Readme.pm subroutines can return the following exit codes:
.PP
.Vb 4
\&  _ERR_USAGE         1   usage errors
\&  _ERR_SCRIPT        2   script or module bug
\&  _ERR_OPENFH        6   failure to open file handles
\&  _ERR_STDIN         16  reading keyboard input failed
.Ve
